CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 5, 1963, pg. 1, reads: "ON DUTY - Pickets of the United Negro Protest Committee wind their way up Braddock Ave. past the headquarters of Mine Safety Appliances. The marchers walked in front of the plant, on Tuesday, and then resumed their picketing at 1 P.M. on Wednesday (today). - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: NAACP Protesters carrying signs protesting employment discrimination, outside Mine Safety Appliance Company on Braddock Avenue, Homewood
